    <text type="letter">
        <body>

            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.01848.001.jpg" type="recto"/>

            <note type="authorial" place="top">Send <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/></note>

            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <date when="1875"><gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> 1875.</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Walt Whitman <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/></salute>
            </opener>


            <p><gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> <unclear reason="illegible" resp="#nhg" cert="low">of this</unclear> letter, I wish you to know that this <gap
                    reason="illegible" unit="char" extent="2 words"/> what might fairly be called a
                backwoods country, and with no means naturally at hand to learn the <hi
                    rend="underline">etiquette</hi> of "society", I yet fully understand the nature
                of my acquaintance with you&#8212;it is a sort of "literary" <unclear
                    reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#km">acquaintance</unclear>
                <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> I would not <unclear reason="illegible"
                    cert="medium" resp="#km">fear</unclear>
                <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> into <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>
                <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#km">rec</unclear><gap
                    reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>
                <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#km">friend</unclear> <gap
                    reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>
                taken <gap
                    reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>
                <unclear reason="illegible" cert="high" resp="#km">sheet of</unclear> <gap
                    reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> no <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>
                <hi rend="underline">throughout</hi> <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> <unclear
                    reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#nhg">don't be</unclear>
                <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"
                    /> gentlemanly to present one's self with some boldness in that way. The strongest of
                my motives all along has been to <hi rend="underline">give you pleasure and be
                    paying back</hi> for what I have received. Yet I have also thought of <hi
                    rend="underline">a good moral effect on my family</hi>
                <unclear reason="illegible" cert="high" resp="#km">from their seeing</unclear> their 
                <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>nition from <gap
                    reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>e in my <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>
                of <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> yet <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>
                might <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>
                <hi rend="underline">insane</hi> or a <hi rend="underline">drunk</hi>
                man <gap reason="illegible" extent="one or two words"/>
                <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#km"><hi rend="underline"
                    >then</hi></unclear> doubted whether you could admit the possibility of such
                conditions producing such <hi rend="underline">sanely</hi> insane writing.</p>

            <p>(P.S. I know <hi rend="underline">you must think</hi> there has been a "level-headed"
                    <hi rend="underline">theory</hi> to my life.)</p>

            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.01848.002.jpg" type="verso"/>

            <p><gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>
                <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#km">occasionally</unclear> that
                    <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#km">you</unclear>
                <hi rend="underline"><unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#km"
                        >still</unclear></hi> live&#8212;for the <hi rend="underline">Scripture</hi>
                says "the dead know not anything, nor is there any more a reward for them &amp;c
                &amp;c. A mere Postal card can tell me that. But if you get tired of writing that
                sort of letters only, I will tell you what more to write of. First tell me of some
                of <hi rend="underline">the things that make you happy</hi>, or at least <hi
                    rend="underline"><unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#km">all
                        about</unclear></hi> your distressed condition. <choice>
                    <sic>Dont</sic>
                    <corr>Don't</corr>
                </choice> you <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> thing about the Centennial <gap
                    reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> expect <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>
                of the <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> John <gap reason="illegible"
                    extent="unk"/> is it <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>
                all the good things of
                    <gap reason="illegible" extent="one word"/>and <unclear reason="illegible"
                    cert="medium" resp="#nhg">with you</unclear> are you now only <hi
                    rend="underline">enduring</hi> life? Please forgive me if I be now
                impertinent&#8212;I have not been so in <hi rend="underline">asking questions</hi>
                before, and I <hi rend="underline"><choice>
                        <sic>cant</sic>
                        <corr>can't</corr>
                    </choice> compel</hi> you to answer.</p>

            <p>Your card of July 2 acknowledged my letter of June 27, but didn't mention my letters
                of June 10 or 12&#8212;I like to know <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> from
                me, in <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> sound <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"
                /> of what <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>
                <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#km">audience</unclear>
                <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> not to <unclear reason="illegible"
                    cert="medium" resp="#km">write</unclear>
                <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> questions <gap reason="illegible"
                    extent="unk" unit="chars" quantity="30"/>, because while my <hi rend="underline"
                    >original and unprompted ideas</hi> would necessarily in most cases be <hi
                    rend="underline">only a repetition</hi>
                <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc.01848.003.jpg" type="recto"/> of what others <gap
                    reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>
                <hi rend="underline">long</hi> ago, or t<gap reason="illegible"
                    extent="one or two words"/> and <hi rend="underline"><gap reason="illegible"
                        extent="one word"/></hi>
                <gap reason="illegible" extent="one word"/> civilization and mastering it".
                Therefore I must not be in a hurry to commence on such things and be giving you my
                "meagre" thoughts.</p>

            <p>I think what will please you best, will be for me to write about myself, my
                circumstances, my <hi rend="underline"><unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium"
                        resp="#km">practical</unclear></hi> philosophy, my mother, father, and
                    <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#km">others</unclear>
                <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> Yet I <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>
                not <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>
                <hi rend="underline">ma</hi><gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> B<gap
                    reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>
                <hi rend="underline">eccent</hi><gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>
                <hi rend="underline">so free</hi><gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> me. My
                eccentricity lies in my adherence to <hi rend="underline">all Nature</hi> and <hi
                    rend="underline">my own nature</hi> and following the straight path of <hi
                    rend="underline">good practical common sense</hi> in such a way as most people
                are not capable of. You and I, <hi rend="underline">you and I</hi> "fly the flight
                of the fluid and swallowing soul, and our <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> of
                    <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/><unclear reason="illegible" cert="low"
                    resp="#nhg">underst</unclear><gap reason="illegible" extent="unk" unit="chars"
                    quantity="27"/> i<gap reason="illegible" extent="unk" unit="chars" quantity="32"/>
                <unclear reason="illegible" cert="high" resp="#km">wise</unclear>
                <gap reason="illegible"/> fool for <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> on in
                this <unclear reason="illegible" resp="#nhg" cert="low">way</unclear>&#8212;<gap reason="illegible"
                    extent="one or two words"/> am not at all <gap reason="illegible" extent="one word"
                /> or <hi rend="underline">contentious and seldom have an enemy</hi>, there is yet in
                    my nature (which
                I can't help) so much of the principle of <hi rend="underline">destructiveness</hi>
                or <hi rend="underline">mortal revenge</hi> that I am constantly <pb
                    xml:id="leaf002v" facs="loc.01848.004.jpg" type="verso"/>
                <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> upon me the <unclear reason="illegible"
                    cert="medium" resp="#nhg">fatal</unclear>
                <gap reason="illegible" extent="one or two words"/> and very <unclear
                    reason="illegible" cert="high" resp="#km">injurious</unclear> provocation. Also
                (so much the worse for me) I have always had a leaning towards <hi rend="underline"
                    >suicide</hi> as a relief in case of great trouble&#8212;Walt! can you require
                absolutely of me as a condition of friendship that I shall change the deepest
                grounded elements of my <hi rend="underline">nature</hi>? "Can the leopard change
                his spots, or the Ethiopian his skin?"</p>

            <p>I think <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> you with <gap reason="illegible"
                    extent="unk"/> <unclear reason="illegible" resp="#nhg" cert="medium">natural</unclear> philosopher, <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>mar<gap
                    reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> together 3 yrs. <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"
                />bined in <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> would be quite a <gap
                    reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> only 8&#8212;to <gap reason="illegible"
                    extent="unk"/> a sort of patent of nobility here if I can judge rightly of
                appearances.&#8212;</p>

            <p>I have got along mighty well with my crop, and hindered the boys from school very
                little so far&#8212;they stand at the head of their classes&#8212;<hi
                    rend="underline">by divine right.</hi></p>

            <p>Little Walt at the age of 7 months &amp; 20 days commenced very suddenly to crawl
                over the floor in "<gap reason="illegible" extent="one word"/>" style <gap
                    reason="illegible" extent="one or two words"/> ago&#8212;<gap reason="illegible"
                    extent="one or two words"/> 18 <unclear reason="illegible" cert="high" resp="#km"
                    >1874</unclear>&#8212; <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/>, and <gap
                        reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> <unclear reason="illegible" resp="#nhg" cert="low">skinned)</unclear> <gap reason="illegible"
                    extent="three lines"/> improve my <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> this
                    <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#nhg">requires oft</unclear> "laying
                by" the crop. What <gap reason="illegible" extent="one word"/>
                <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#km">are most</unclear>
                <gap reason="illegible" extent="unk"/> seem to be agreed that what America and the
                world need is to have not saints or angels but merely <hi rend="underline">good
                    enough</hi> people and allowing some difference in directions of action.</p>



            <closer>
                <signed>J. N. J.</signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
